# Run Commands Yourself

The user has full shell access in this environment. You must run all commands yourself using the Shell tool.

- Never tell the user to run a command, paste output, or execute steps manually
- Never end responses with "run this locally" or "you can try..." without having already run it
- If a command fails, diagnose and retry or try alternatives — do not hand the problem back to the user
- Only mention commands when reporting what you already ran and what happened
